race.comment: Competitive betting race for a Wednesday with four last start winners going head-to-head. TAHNEE TERRITORY (9) is one of them, having knocked off her maiden at Gawler last start. She's up to 1200m and drawn wide here, although Kayla Crowther rides this track well and should give her a chance to win. She can go on with it. SCANDALIST (12) is first-up and, while she generally takes a run or two to hit her straps, the fact she's straight out to 1200m makes me think she's a big chance fresh. She maps to get the run of the race for Opperman. LAYIN' UP (10) scored an overdue win in a modest maiden last start but that might be the confidence booster she needs to go on with it now. She's drawn to get the favours. Others for exotics might be ROYAL SCRIPTURE (2) and CREEK (4).
